Biography

Irene Schouten is a Dutch speed skater and cyclist. Born on June 15, 1992, she has become a prominent figure in both sports. Known for her endurance and determination, Irene has won numerous medals in international competitions, including the Winter Olympics and World Championships. Her passion for sports and relentless pursuit of excellence continue to inspire athletes around the world.
